category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Kolonok (zool.), Siberian Weasel


"The less a man carries in his pack, the more he must carry in his head" - Horace Kephart


Have you ever thought about what you would do if you became lost while on a day hike? How about if you injured yourself out from civilization and were unable to move? Then, all too quickly dusk approaches and the realization that you will be spending the night in the wilderness begins to sets in. Being prepared for this type of situation and having a well established plan could mean the difference between life and death. That is why at the “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup, our chief aim is to help people build their knowledge of wilderness survival skills.

The Aim of this Meetup Group is to teach you the skills needed to survive and thrive in the wilderness and woodlands.  You will learn the skills and techniques to light fires, identify edible plants, build shelters, make traps and snares, purify water, prepare rabbit, fish and birds, use knives and saws safely and efficiently and navigate around the country.

Upon leaning these skills members will understand how to: become self sufficient in the wilderness, formulate a concrete plan to getting rescued safely when lost or injured and build outdoor leadership/confidence skills.

The “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup strongly believe a subject must be mastered before it can be taught; therefore, my teaching methods have been developed through years of education, practice, experiences and dedication of me and I will structure our lesson around a fundamental survival principle commonly known as the Rules of 3.

So what is the Rules of 3?

The rules of 3 are the guidelines that states you cannot survive more than:

• 3 Minutes without air

• 3 Hours without shelter or proper clothing

• 3 Days without water

• 3 Weeks without food


Classes we host:

• Wilderness Survival Kits

• Shelter Building

• Wild Edible Plants

• Tracking

• Fire Starting

• Water Purification

• Land Navigation

• First Aid

• Self defense

And much much more…

Important notice:

• This is not a group for "Meetup Group collectors"

• We are a group of active members

• Members who are not actively participating are not eligible

• Members who do not actively participate are automatically excluded


Minimum age

• The minimum age is 18 years, or 10 years if acompanied by at least one responsible adult!!!

• Participants must be able to handle safetly a KNIFE and FIRE.


Responsibility and liability

• Kolonok Bushcraft Survival or I, assume no liability for accidents or damage. Insurance and 3th part liability is the responsibility of each individual participant or legal representative.

• With the registration you accept this term or condition.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
This platform proposes to share info and experiences in construction with natural materials. And occasionally give a hand on your building site. I have learnt several techniques to build a house with natural materials, and I wish to spread this knowledge to anyone interested in living in a more healthy and natural environment.
We will discuss: clay plasters, lime mortar and lime plasters, natural fibers as insulation, how to build walls without cement, the plus and minus of Tadelakt bathrooms, natural paints, dry stone wall for your garden, straw bale walls, rammed earth walls.
We will discuss where to get natural materials, which one to get, and others on the market that are not 100% natural.
This knowledge is best when you repair an ancient house, or build a new natural house, but it can also be applied to a "modern house" that is not really natural.
Anyone who has experienced in this field is here welcome to share its knowledge too.
Looking forward to meeting you,
Peace,

The group aims to exchange techniques, ideas and opportunities in the filed of aerial cinematography. The plan is as follows: 

First meeting: Get to know each other and plan a drone-trip (1 day) to a location where we can try out new techniques and explore our drones (e.g. Swiss mountains).

Second meeting: Day-trip to a location where it is legal, safe and pretty to fly out drones This group is aimed for professional or semi-professional drone pilots in Switzerland, whatever that means ;-). description:

We are also on Facebook: Social Fabric page and Social Fabric group – like and join!

On Twitter we are @iamsocialfabric.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Ikebana ist eine Form der Schulung, die Einblick in die Schönheit des Lebens gewährt.

Ikebana Schule Caroline Vögele-Ott

Dies ist eine Gruppe für alle die sich gerne mit Blumen, natürlichem Pflanzenmaterial und schönen Gefässen beschäftigen und eine sinnliche Beziehung zur Natur pflegen. Ob Anfänger oder Fortgeschritten, alle sind willkommen, entweder meine Anfängerkurse zu besuchen oder in der Erfahrungsgruppe mitzumachen. Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, um Ikebana allen Interessierten ohne Vorkenntnisse zugänglich zu machen und die bereits erfahrenen IkebanistiInnen zum Austausch und gemeinsamen Experimentieren zu ermuntern. Ich freue mich auf viel sinnliche, blumige und kreative Meetings und kleine Erleuchtungsmomente für Anfänger.

Ich selber nehem regelmässig an verschiedenen internationalen Workshops teil und bilde mich immer weiter. Wer einmal erlebt hat wie wertvoll dieses schaffen mit Blumen und Zweigen ist, kann für den Rest seines Lebens nicht mehr davon ablassen. So ist es mir gegangen, als ich vor über 12 Jahren angefangen habe. Es wird Teil des Alltags. Die Betrachtung und die Wahrnehmung der Natur wird zu einem bereichernden Erlebnis. Der Wunsch nach Ordnung im eigenen Wohnraum ist eine Nebenerscheinung die Ikebana ganz unbemerkt fördert und entstehen lässt. Für mich ist Ikebana auch eine Form von "urban Gardening". Sie bringt einen Ausschnitt der Natrur in Deinen Wohnraum und verzaubert ihn jedes Mal von neuem! 

Bitte finde auf folgendem Link noch ausführlichere Informationen zu meiner Schule:

http://www.caroline-voegele.ch/index.php?id...

Herzlichst

Caroline
name: Zürich Ohara Ikebana, the art of japanese flower arrangement

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Kolonok (zool.), Siberian Weasel


"The less a man carries in his pack, the more he must carry in his head" - Horace Kephart


Have you ever thought about what you would do if you became lost while on a day hike? How about if you injured yourself out from civilization and were unable to move? Then, all too quickly dusk approaches and the realization that you will be spending the night in the wilderness begins to sets in. Being prepared for this type of situation and having a well established plan could mean the difference between life and death. That is why at the “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup, our chief aim is to help people build their knowledge of wilderness survival skills.

The Aim of this Meetup Group is to teach you the skills needed to survive and thrive in the wilderness and woodlands.  You will learn the skills and techniques to light fires, identify edible plants, build shelters, make traps and snares, purify water, prepare rabbit, fish and birds, use knives and saws safely and efficiently and navigate around the country.

Upon leaning these skills members will understand how to: become self sufficient in the wilderness, formulate a concrete plan to getting rescued safely when lost or injured and build outdoor leadership/confidence skills.

The “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup strongly believe a subject must be mastered before it can be taught; therefore, my teaching methods have been developed through years of education, practice, experiences and dedication of me and I will structure our lesson around a fundamental survival principle commonly known as the Rules of 3.

So what is the Rules of 3?

The rules of 3 are the guidelines that states you cannot survive more than:

• 3 Minutes without air

• 3 Hours without shelter or proper clothing

• 3 Days without water

• 3 Weeks without food


Classes we host:

• Wilderness Survival Kits

• Shelter Building

• Wild Edible Plants

• Tracking

• Fire Starting

• Water Purification

• Land Navigation

• First Aid

• Self defense

And much much more…

Important notice:

• This is not a group for "Meetup Group collectors"

• We are a group of active members

• Members who are not actively participating are not eligible

• Members who do not actively participate are automatically excluded


Minimum age

• The minimum age is 18 years, or 10 years if acompanied by at least one responsible adult!!!

• Participants must be able to handle safetly a KNIFE and FIRE.


Responsibility and liability

• Kolonok Bushcraft Survival or I, assume no liability for accidents or damage. Insurance and 3th part liability is the responsibility of each individual participant or legal representative.

• With the registration you accept this term or condition.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
This platform proposes to share info and experiences in construction with natural materials. And occasionally give a hand on your building site. I have learnt several techniques to build a house with natural materials, and I wish to spread this knowledge to anyone interested in living in a more healthy and natural environment.
We will discuss: clay plasters, lime mortar and lime plasters, natural fibers as insulation, how to build walls without cement, the plus and minus of Tadelakt bathrooms, natural paints, dry stone wall for your garden, straw bale walls, rammed earth walls.
We will discuss where to get natural materials, which one to get, and others on the market that are not 100% natural.
This knowledge is best when you repair an ancient house, or build a new natural house, but it can also be applied to a "modern house" that is not really natural.
Anyone who has experienced in this field is here welcome to share its knowledge too.
Looking forward to meeting you,
Peace,
Catherine

The group aims to exchange techniques, ideas and opportunities in the filed of aerial cinematography. The plan is as follows: 

First meeting: Get to know each other and plan a drone-trip (1 day) to a location where we can try out new techniques and explore our drones (e.g. Swiss mountains).

Second meeting: Day-trip to a location where it is legal, safe and pretty to fly out drones This group is aimed for professional or semi-professional drone pilots in Switzerland, whatever that means ;-). I own a DJI Inspire 2 X7 16 mm and am looking for other enthusiasts to fly with and share knowledge :-)

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Vous aimez la décoration d’intérieur, les tendances déco, l’aménagement d’intérieur, vous voulez que votre intérieur vous ressemble et soit unique, mais vous vous heurtez à un marché qui propose des milliers de solutions et vous êtes parfois perdu(e)s dans tout ce choix.

J’aide les personnes comme vous qui veulent faire de leur espace de vie un intérieur unique et harmonieux, je les accompagne pour qu’elles aient la fierté de le réaliser elle-même.

Passionnée par ce métier de coach déco, je vous propose de passer un bon moment ensemble à partager sur des problématiques que l’on rencontre quand on veut aménager, valoriser son intérieur.

J’ai donc créé pour vous
---- LES MERCREDIS POUR MON ESPACE DE VIE ----

-. 1 mercredi par mois
-. 1 thème
-. Une discussion en toute décontraction sur vos problématiques sur le thème du mois
-. Des solutions pratiques et simples à appliquées.

Je me réjouis de vous rencontrer !

A bientôt

Floriane
Révélatrice d’espace de vie

description:
This is a group for anybody who loves sewing and textile work. Social Fabric (www.socialfabric.ch) is a community oriented-place in Zürich that supports the use of textiles and clothing that have a small ecological and social footprint. At Social Fabric, we offer courses and community events that help people to build a new relationship to their clothes. 

We also have a project that supports refugee integration by encouraging refugees to create and develop their own products that have a textile-oriented theme. Our long term goal with this project is to both employ refugees as producers, and to enable refugee entrepreneurs. 

We are also on Facebook: Social Fabric page and Social Fabric group – like and join!

On Twitter we are @iamsocialfabric.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Ikebana ist eine Form der Schulung, die Einblick in die Schönheit des Lebens gewährt.

Ikebana Schule Caroline Vögele-Ott

Dies ist eine Gruppe für alle die sich gerne mit Blumen, natürlichem Pflanzenmaterial und schönen Gefässen beschäftigen und eine sinnliche Beziehung zur Natur pflegen. Ob Anfänger oder Fortgeschritten, alle sind willkommen, entweder meine Anfängerkurse zu besuchen oder in der Erfahrungsgruppe mitzumachen. Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, um Ikebana allen Interessierten ohne Vorkenntnisse zugänglich zu machen und die bereits erfahrenen IkebanistiInnen zum Austausch und gemeinsamen Experimentieren zu ermuntern. Ich freue mich auf viel sinnliche, blumige und kreative Meetings und kleine Erleuchtungsmomente für Anfänger.

Ich selber nehem regelmässig an verschiedenen internationalen Workshops teil und bilde mich immer weiter. Wer einmal erlebt hat wie wertvoll dieses schaffen mit Blumen und Zweigen ist, kann für den Rest seines Lebens nicht mehr davon ablassen. So ist es mir gegangen, als ich vor über 12 Jahren angefangen habe. Es wird Teil des Alltags. Die Betrachtung und die Wahrnehmung der Natur wird zu einem bereichernden Erlebnis. Der Wunsch nach Ordnung im eigenen Wohnraum ist eine Nebenerscheinung die Ikebana ganz unbemerkt fördert und entstehen lässt. Für mich ist Ikebana auch eine Form von "urban Gardening". Sie bringt einen Ausschnitt der Natrur in Deinen Wohnraum und verzaubert ihn jedes Mal von neuem! 

Bitte finde auf folgendem Link noch ausführlichere Informationen zu meiner Schule:

http://www.caroline-voegele.ch/index.php?id...

Herzlichst

Caroline
name: Zürich Ohara Ikebana, the art of japanese flower arrangement

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Kolonok (zool.), Siberian Weasel


"The less a man carries in his pack, the more he must carry in his head" - Horace Kephart


Have you ever thought about what you would do if you became lost while on a day hike? How about if you injured yourself out from civilization and were unable to move? Then, all too quickly dusk approaches and the realization that you will be spending the night in the wilderness begins to sets in. Being prepared for this type of situation and having a well established plan could mean the difference between life and death. That is why at the “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup, our chief aim is to help people build their knowledge of wilderness survival skills.

The Aim of this Meetup Group is to teach you the skills needed to survive and thrive in the wilderness and woodlands.  You will learn the skills and techniques to light fires, identify edible plants, build shelters, make traps and snares, purify water, prepare rabbit, fish and birds, use knives and saws safely and efficiently and navigate around the country.

Upon leaning these skills members will understand how to: become self sufficient in the wilderness, formulate a concrete plan to getting rescued safely when lost or injured and build outdoor leadership/confidence skills.

The “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup strongly believe a subject must be mastered before it can be taught; therefore, my teaching methods have been developed through years of education, practice, experiences and dedication of me and I will structure our lesson around a fundamental survival principle commonly known as the Rules of 3.

So what is the Rules of 3?

The rules of 3 are the guidelines that states you cannot survive more than:

• 3 Minutes without air

• 3 Hours without shelter or proper clothing

• 3 Days without water

• 3 Weeks without food


Classes we host:

• Wilderness Survival Kits

• Shelter Building

• Wild Edible Plants

• Tracking

• Fire Starting

• Water Purification

• Land Navigation

• First Aid

• Self defense

And much much more…

Important notice:

• This is not a group for "Meetup Group collectors"

• We are a group of active members

• Members who are not actively participating are not eligible

• Members who do not actively participate are automatically excluded


Minimum age

• The minimum age is 18 years, or 10 years if acompanied by at least one responsible adult!!!

• Participants must be able to handle safetly a KNIFE and FIRE.


Responsibility and liability

• Kolonok Bushcraft Survival or I, assume no liability for accidents or damage. Insurance and 3th part liability is the responsibility of each individual participant or legal representative.

• With the registration you accept this term or condition.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
This platform proposes to share info and experiences in construction with natural materials. And occasionally give a hand on your building site. I have learnt several techniques to build a house with natural materials, and I wish to spread this knowledge to anyone interested in living in a more healthy and natural environment.
We will discuss: clay plasters, lime mortar and lime plasters, natural fibers as insulation, how to build walls without cement, the plus and minus of Tadelakt bathrooms, natural paints, dry stone wall for your garden, straw bale walls, rammed earth walls.
We will discuss where to get natural materials, which one to get, and others on the market that are not 100% natural.
This knowledge is best when you repair an ancient house, or build a new natural house, but it can also be applied to a "modern house" that is not really natural.
Anyone who has experienced in this field is here welcome to share its knowledge too.
Looking forward to meeting you,
Peace,
Catherine
name: Build your natural house!

description:
This is a group for anybody who loves sewing and textile work. Social Fabric (www.socialfabric.ch) is a community oriented-place in Zürich that supports the use of textiles and clothing that have a small ecological and social footprint. At Social Fabric, we offer courses and community events that help people to build a new relationship to their clothes. 

We also have a project that supports refugee integration by encouraging refugees to create and develop their own products that have a textile-oriented theme. Our long term goal with this project is to both employ refugees as producers, and to enable refugee entrepreneurs. 

We are also on Facebook: Social Fabric page and Social Fabric group – like and join!

On Twitter we are @iamsocialfabric.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Ikebana ist eine Form der Schulung, die Einblick in die Schönheit des Lebens gewährt.

Ikebana Schule Caroline Vögele-Ott

Dies ist eine Gruppe für alle die sich gerne mit Blumen, natürlichem Pflanzenmaterial und schönen Gefässen beschäftigen und eine sinnliche Beziehung zur Natur pflegen. Ob Anfänger oder Fortgeschritten, alle sind willkommen, entweder meine Anfängerkurse zu besuchen oder in der Erfahrungsgruppe mitzumachen. Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, um Ikebana allen Interessierten ohne Vorkenntnisse zugänglich zu machen und die bereits erfahrenen IkebanistiInnen zum Austausch und gemeinsamen Experimentieren zu ermuntern. Ich freue mich auf viel sinnliche, blumige und kreative Meetings und kleine Erleuchtungsmomente für Anfänger.

Ich selber nehem regelmässig an verschiedenen internationalen Workshops teil und bilde mich immer weiter. Wer einmal erlebt hat wie wertvoll dieses schaffen mit Blumen und Zweigen ist, kann für den Rest seines Lebens nicht mehr davon ablassen. So ist es mir gegangen, als ich vor über 12 Jahren angefangen habe. Es wird Teil des Alltags. Die Betrachtung und die Wahrnehmung der Natur wird zu einem bereichernden Erlebnis. Der Wunsch nach Ordnung im eigenen Wohnraum ist eine Nebenerscheinung die Ikebana ganz unbemerkt fördert und entstehen lässt. Für mich ist Ikebana auch eine Form von "urban Gardening". Sie bringt einen Ausschnitt der Natrur in Deinen Wohnraum und verzaubert ihn jedes Mal von neuem! 

Bitte finde auf folgendem Link noch ausführlichere Informationen zu meiner Schule:

http://www.caroline-voegele.ch/index.php?id...

Herzlichst

Caroline
name: Zürich Ohara Ikebana, the art of japanese flower arrangement

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Kolonok (zool.), Siberian Weasel


"The less a man carries in his pack, the more he must carry in his head" - Horace Kephart


Have you ever thought about what you would do if you became lost while on a day hike? How about if you injured yourself out from civilization and were unable to move? Then, all too quickly dusk approaches and the realization that you will be spending the night in the wilderness begins to sets in. Being prepared for this type of situation and having a well established plan could mean the difference between life and death. That is why at the “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup, our chief aim is to help people build their knowledge of wilderness survival skills.

The Aim of this Meetup Group is to teach you the skills needed to survive and thrive in the wilderness and woodlands.  You will learn the skills and techniques to light fires, identify edible plants, build shelters, make traps and snares, purify water, prepare rabbit, fish and birds, use knives and saws safely and efficiently and navigate around the country.

Upon leaning these skills members will understand how to: become self sufficient in the wilderness, formulate a concrete plan to getting rescued safely when lost or injured and build outdoor leadership/confidence skills.

The “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup strongly believe a subject must be mastered before it can be taught; therefore, my teaching methods have been developed through years of education, practice, experiences and dedication of me and I will structure our lesson around a fundamental survival principle commonly known as the Rules of 3.

So what is the Rules of 3?

The rules of 3 are the guidelines that states you cannot survive more than:

• 3 Minutes without air

• 3 Hours without shelter or proper clothing

• 3 Days without water

• 3 Weeks without food


Classes we host:

• Wilderness Survival Kits

• Shelter Building

• Wild Edible Plants

• Tracking

• Fire Starting

• Water Purification

• Land Navigation

• First Aid

• Self defense

And much much more…

Important notice:

• This is not a group for "Meetup Group collectors"

• We are a group of active members

• Members who are not actively participating are not eligible

• Members who do not actively participate are automatically excluded


Minimum age

• The minimum age is 18 years, or 10 years if acompanied by at least one responsible adult!!!

• Participants must be able to handle safetly a KNIFE and FIRE.


Responsibility and liability

• Kolonok Bushcraft Survival or I, assume no liability for accidents or damage. Insurance and 3th part liability is the responsibility of each individual participant or legal representative.

• With the registration you accept this term or condition.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
This platform proposes to share info and experiences in construction with natural materials. And occasionally give a hand on your building site. I have learnt several techniques to build a house with natural materials, and I wish to spread this knowledge to anyone interested in living in a more healthy and natural environment.
We will discuss: clay plasters, lime mortar and lime plasters, natural fibers as insulation, how to build walls without cement, the plus and minus of Tadelakt bathrooms, natural paints, dry stone wall for your garden, straw bale walls, rammed earth walls.
We will discuss where to get natural materials, which one to get, and others on the market that are not 100% natural.
This knowledge is best when you repair an ancient house, or build a new natural house, but it can also be applied to a "modern house" that is not really natural.
Anyone who has experienced in this field is here welcome to share its knowledge too.
Looking forward to meeting you,
Peace,
Catherine

The group aims to exchange techniques, ideas and opportunities in the filed of aerial cinematography. The plan is as follows: 

First meeting: Get to know each other and plan a drone-trip (1 day) to a location where we can try out new techniques and explore our drones (e.g. Swiss mountains).

Second meeting: Day-trip to a location where it is legal, safe and pretty to fly out drones This group is aimed for professional or semi-professional drone pilots in Switzerland, whatever that means ;-). I own a DJI Inspire 2 X7 16 mm and am looking for other enthusiasts to fly with and share knowledge :-)

description:
This is a group for anybody who loves sewing and textile work. Social Fabric (www.socialfabric.ch) is a community oriented-place in Zürich that supports the use of textiles and clothing that have a small ecological and social footprint. At Social Fabric, we offer courses and community events that help people to build a new relationship to their clothes. 

We also have a project that supports refugee integration by encouraging refugees to create and develop their own products that have a textile-oriented theme. Our long term goal with this project is to both employ refugees as producers, and to enable refugee entrepreneurs. 

We are also on Facebook: Social Fabric page and Social Fabric group – like and join!

On Twitter we are @iamsocialfabric.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Ikebana ist eine Form der Schulung, die Einblick in die Schönheit des Lebens gewährt.

Ikebana Schule Caroline Vögele-Ott

Dies ist eine Gruppe für alle die sich gerne mit Blumen, natürlichem Pflanzenmaterial und schönen Gefässen beschäftigen und eine sinnliche Beziehung zur Natur pflegen. Ob Anfänger oder Fortgeschritten, alle sind willkommen, entweder meine Anfängerkurse zu besuchen oder in der Erfahrungsgruppe mitzumachen. Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, um Ikebana allen Interessierten ohne Vorkenntnisse zugänglich zu machen und die bereits erfahrenen IkebanistiInnen zum Austausch und gemeinsamen Experimentieren zu ermuntern. Ich freue mich auf viel sinnliche, blumige und kreative Meetings und kleine Erleuchtungsmomente für Anfänger.

Ich selber nehem regelmässig an verschiedenen internationalen Workshops teil und bilde mich immer weiter. Wer einmal erlebt hat wie wertvoll dieses schaffen mit Blumen und Zweigen ist, kann für den Rest seines Lebens nicht mehr davon ablassen. So ist es mir gegangen, als ich vor über 12 Jahren angefangen habe. Es wird Teil des Alltags. Die Betrachtung und die Wahrnehmung der Natur wird zu einem bereichernden Erlebnis. Der Wunsch nach Ordnung im eigenen Wohnraum ist eine Nebenerscheinung die Ikebana ganz unbemerkt fördert und entstehen lässt. Für mich ist Ikebana auch eine Form von "urban Gardening". Sie bringt einen Ausschnitt der Natrur in Deinen Wohnraum und verzaubert ihn jedes Mal von neuem! 

Bitte finde auf folgendem Link noch ausführlichere Informationen zu meiner Schule:

http://www.caroline-voegele.ch/index.php?id...

Herzlichst

Caroline
name: Zürich Ohara Ikebana, the art of japanese flower arrangement

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Kolonok (zool.), Siberian Weasel


"The less a man carries in his pack, the more he must carry in his head" - Horace Kephart


Have you ever thought about what you would do if you became lost while on a day hike? How about if you injured yourself out from civilization and were unable to move? Then, all too quickly dusk approaches and the realization that you will be spending the night in the wilderness begins to sets in. Being prepared for this type of situation and having a well established plan could mean the difference between life and death. That is why at the “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup, our chief aim is to help people build their knowledge of wilderness survival skills.

The Aim of this Meetup Group is to teach you the skills needed to survive and thrive in the wilderness and woodlands.  You will learn the skills and techniques to light fires, identify edible plants, build shelters, make traps and snares, purify water, prepare rabbit, fish and birds, use knives and saws safely and efficiently and navigate around the country.

Upon leaning these skills members will understand how to: become self sufficient in the wilderness, formulate a concrete plan to getting rescued safely when lost or injured and build outdoor leadership/confidence skills.

The “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup strongly believe a subject must be mastered before it can be taught; therefore, my teaching methods have been developed through years of education, practice, experiences and dedication of me and I will structure our lesson around a fundamental survival principle commonly known as the Rules of 3.

So what is the Rules of 3?

The rules of 3 are the guidelines that states you cannot survive more than:

• 3 Minutes without air

• 3 Hours without shelter or proper clothing

• 3 Days without water

• 3 Weeks without food


Classes we host:

• Wilderness Survival Kits

• Shelter Building

• Wild Edible Plants

• Tracking

• Fire Starting

• Water Purification

• Land Navigation

• First Aid

• Self defense

And much much more…

Important notice:

• This is not a group for "Meetup Group collectors"

• We are a group of active members

• Members who are not actively participating are not eligible

• Members who do not actively participate are automatically excluded


Minimum age

• The minimum age is 18 years, or 10 years if acompanied by at least one responsible adult!!!

• Participants must be able to handle safetly a KNIFE and FIRE.


Responsibility and liability

• Kolonok Bushcraft Survival or I, assume no liability for accidents or damage. Insurance and 3th part liability is the responsibility of each individual participant or legal representative.

• With the registration you accept this term or condition.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
This platform proposes to share info and experiences in construction with natural materials. And occasionally give a hand on your building site. I have learnt several techniques to build a house with natural materials, and I wish to spread this knowledge to anyone interested in living in a more healthy and natural environment.
We will discuss: clay plasters, lime mortar and lime plasters, natural fibers as insulation, how to build walls without cement, the plus and minus of Tadelakt bathrooms, natural paints, dry stone wall for your garden, straw bale walls, rammed earth walls.
We will discuss where to get natural materials, which one to get, and others on the market that are not 100% natural.
This knowledge is best when you repair an ancient house, or build a new natural house, but it can also be applied to a "modern house" that is not really natural.
Anyone who has experienced in this field is here welcome to share its knowledge too.
Looking forward to meeting you,
Peace,
Catherine
name: Build your natural house!

The group aims to exchange techniques, ideas and opportunities in the filed of aerial cinematography. The plan is as follows: 

First meeting: Get to know each other and plan a drone-trip (1 day) to a location where we can try out new techniques and explore our drones (e.g. Swiss mountains).

Second meeting: Day-trip to a location where it is legal, safe and pretty to fly out drones This group is aimed for professional or semi-professional drone pilots in Switzerland, whatever that means ;-). I own a DJI Inspire 2 X7 16 mm and am looking for other enthusiasts to fly with and share knowledge :-)

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Could this be you?: "Hi, my name is Bob, and I'm a CNC-builder-aholic." Alone, struggling to turn a CNC dream into some kind of reality? Trying to figure out which is the best ball or ACME screw, linear rail, stepper or servo system, Makerslide or Bosch-Rexroth profile, epoxy concrete base or MDF, Chinese high speed spindle or Kress router or diy brushless motor hack, ... (you know the list goes on).  Finally a support group for those suffering from this condition. Maybe together we can push our designs from our heads to our benchtops.

Although 3D printers could technically be called a computer numerically controlled device, this group is more about machines pushing more or much more weight--a milling device/router, a plasma cutter, a laser cutter, etc.  3D printers are also interesting to discuss but wouldn't be the main focus..
name: CNC Builders Basel

description:
This is a group for anybody who loves sewing and textile work. Social Fabric (www.socialfabric.ch) is a community oriented-place in Zürich that supports the use of textiles and clothing that have a small ecological and social footprint. At Social Fabric, we offer courses and community events that help people to build a new relationship to their clothes. 

We also have a project that supports refugee integration by encouraging refugees to create and develop their own products that have a textile-oriented theme. Our long term goal with this project is to both employ refugees as producers, and to enable refugee entrepreneurs. 

We are also on Facebook: Social Fabric page and Social Fabric group – like and join!

On Twitter we are @iamsocialfabric.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Ikebana ist eine Form der Schulung, die Einblick in die Schönheit des Lebens gewährt.

Ikebana Schule Caroline Vögele-Ott

Dies ist eine Gruppe für alle die sich gerne mit Blumen, natürlichem Pflanzenmaterial und schönen Gefässen beschäftigen und eine sinnliche Beziehung zur Natur pflegen. Ob Anfänger oder Fortgeschritten, alle sind willkommen, entweder meine Anfängerkurse zu besuchen oder in der Erfahrungsgruppe mitzumachen. Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, um Ikebana allen Interessierten ohne Vorkenntnisse zugänglich zu machen und die bereits erfahrenen IkebanistiInnen zum Austausch und gemeinsamen Experimentieren zu ermuntern. Ich freue mich auf viel sinnliche, blumige und kreative Meetings und kleine Erleuchtungsmomente für Anfänger.

Ich selber nehem regelmässig an verschiedenen internationalen Workshops teil und bilde mich immer weiter. Wer einmal erlebt hat wie wertvoll dieses schaffen mit Blumen und Zweigen ist, kann für den Rest seines Lebens nicht mehr davon ablassen. So ist es mir gegangen, als ich vor über 12 Jahren angefangen habe. Es wird Teil des Alltags. Die Betrachtung und die Wahrnehmung der Natur wird zu einem bereichernden Erlebnis. Der Wunsch nach Ordnung im eigenen Wohnraum ist eine Nebenerscheinung die Ikebana ganz unbemerkt fördert und entstehen lässt. Für mich ist Ikebana auch eine Form von "urban Gardening". Sie bringt einen Ausschnitt der Natrur in Deinen Wohnraum und verzaubert ihn jedes Mal von neuem! 

Bitte finde auf folgendem Link noch ausführlichere Informationen zu meiner Schule:

http://www.caroline-voegele.ch/index.php?id...

Herzlichst

Caroline
name: Zürich Ohara Ikebana, the art of japanese flower arrangement

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Kolonok (zool.), Siberian Weasel


"The less a man carries in his pack, the more he must carry in his head" - Horace Kephart


Have you ever thought about what you would do if you became lost while on a day hike? How about if you injured yourself out from civilization and were unable to move? Then, all too quickly dusk approaches and the realization that you will be spending the night in the wilderness begins to sets in. Being prepared for this type of situation and having a well established plan could mean the difference between life and death. That is why at the “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup, our chief aim is to help people build their knowledge of wilderness survival skills.

The Aim of this Meetup Group is to teach you the skills needed to survive and thrive in the wilderness and woodlands.  You will learn the skills and techniques to light fires, identify edible plants, build shelters, make traps and snares, purify water, prepare rabbit, fish and birds, use knives and saws safely and efficiently and navigate around the country.

Upon leaning these skills members will understand how to: become self sufficient in the wilderness, formulate a concrete plan to getting rescued safely when lost or injured and build outdoor leadership/confidence skills.

The “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup strongly believe a subject must be mastered before it can be taught; therefore, my teaching methods have been developed through years of education, practice, experiences and dedication of me and I will structure our lesson around a fundamental survival principle commonly known as the Rules of 3.

So what is the Rules of 3?

The rules of 3 are the guidelines that states you cannot survive more than:

• 3 Minutes without air

• 3 Hours without shelter or proper clothing

• 3 Days without water

• 3 Weeks without food


Classes we host:

• Wilderness Survival Kits

• Shelter Building

• Wild Edible Plants

• Tracking

• Fire Starting

• Water Purification

• Land Navigation

• First Aid

• Self defense

And much much more…

Important notice:

• This is not a group for "Meetup Group collectors"

• We are a group of active members

• Members who are not actively participating are not eligible

• Members who do not actively participate are automatically excluded


Minimum age

• The minimum age is 18 years, or 10 years if acompanied by at least one responsible adult!!!

• Participants must be able to handle safetly a KNIFE and FIRE.


Responsibility and liability

• Kolonok Bushcraft Survival or I, assume no liability for accidents or damage. Insurance and 3th part liability is the responsibility of each individual participant or legal representative.

• With the registration you accept this term or condition.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
This platform proposes to share info and experiences in construction with natural materials. And occasionally give a hand on your building site. I have learnt several techniques to build a house with natural materials, and I wish to spread this knowledge to anyone interested in living in a more healthy and natural environment.
We will discuss: clay plasters, lime mortar and lime plasters, natural fibers as insulation, how to build walls without cement, the plus and minus of Tadelakt bathrooms, natural paints, dry stone wall for your garden, straw bale walls, rammed earth walls.
We will discuss where to get natural materials, which one to get, and others on the market that are not 100% natural.
This knowledge is best when you repair an ancient house, or build a new natural house, but it can also be applied to a "modern house" that is not really natural.
Anyone who has experienced in this field is here welcome to share its knowledge too.
Looking forward to meeting you,
Peace,
Catherine
name: Build your natural house!

description:
The group aims to exchange techniques, ideas and opportunities in the filed of aerial cinematography. The plan is as follows: 

First meeting: Get to know each other and plan a drone-trip (1 day) to a location where we can try out new techniques and explore our drones (e.g. Swiss mountains).

Second meeting: Day-trip to a location where it is legal, safe and pretty to fly out drones This group is aimed for professional or semi-professional drone pilots in Switzerland, whatever that means ;-). I own a DJI Inspire 2 X7 16 mm and am looking for other enthusiasts to fly with and share knowledge :-)
name: Aerial Cinematography Zurich

description:
TheBeehive is an atelier for kids and women created by two young mothers who are passionate about making things… sewing, painting, working with wood, cement and whatever else they can get their hands on.
The only limits that we fix for ourselves are those of our imagination.
We offer organised workshops for kids (with or without parent) and women throughout the week and on saturdays.
The goal is for women to have a place to go to and create whatever their hearts desire and at the same time network with other women and to have a fun time. And for kids to broaden their imaginations with arts & crafts and make new friends....

description:
This is a group for anybody who loves sewing and textile work. Social Fabric (www.socialfabric.ch) is a community oriented-place in Zürich that supports the use of textiles and clothing that have a small ecological and social footprint. At Social Fabric, we offer courses and community events that help people to build a new relationship to their clothes. 

We also have a project that supports refugee integration by encouraging refugees to create and develop their own products that have a textile-oriented theme. Our long term goal with this project is to both employ refugees as producers, and to enable refugee entrepreneurs. 

We are also on Facebook: Social Fabric page and Social Fabric group – like and join!

On Twitter we are @iamsocialfabric.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Ikebana ist eine Form der Schulung, die Einblick in die Schönheit des Lebens gewährt.

Ikebana Schule Caroline Vögele-Ott

Dies ist eine Gruppe für alle die sich gerne mit Blumen, natürlichem Pflanzenmaterial und schönen Gefässen beschäftigen und eine sinnliche Beziehung zur Natur pflegen. Ob Anfänger oder Fortgeschritten, alle sind willkommen, entweder meine Anfängerkurse zu besuchen oder in der Erfahrungsgruppe mitzumachen. Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, um Ikebana allen Interessierten ohne Vorkenntnisse zugänglich zu machen und die bereits erfahrenen IkebanistiInnen zum Austausch und gemeinsamen Experimentieren zu ermuntern. Ich freue mich auf viel sinnliche, blumige und kreative Meetings und kleine Erleuchtungsmomente für Anfänger.

Ich selber nehem regelmässig an verschiedenen internationalen Workshops teil und bilde mich immer weiter. Wer einmal erlebt hat wie wertvoll dieses schaffen mit Blumen und Zweigen ist, kann für den Rest seines Lebens nicht mehr davon ablassen. So ist es mir gegangen, als ich vor über 12 Jahren angefangen habe. Es wird Teil des Alltags. Die Betrachtung und die Wahrnehmung der Natur wird zu einem bereichernden Erlebnis. Der Wunsch nach Ordnung im eigenen Wohnraum ist eine Nebenerscheinung die Ikebana ganz unbemerkt fördert und entstehen lässt. Für mich ist Ikebana auch eine Form von "urban Gardening". Sie bringt einen Ausschnitt der Natrur in Deinen Wohnraum und verzaubert ihn jedes Mal von neuem! 

Bitte finde auf folgendem Link noch ausführlichere Informationen zu meiner Schule:

http://www.caroline-voegele.ch/index.php?id...

Herzlichst

Caroline
name: Zürich Ohara Ikebana, the art of japanese flower arrangement

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Kolonok (zool.), Siberian Weasel


"The less a man carries in his pack, the more he must carry in his head" - Horace Kephart


Have you ever thought about what you would do if you became lost while on a day hike? How about if you injured yourself out from civilization and were unable to move? Then, all too quickly dusk approaches and the realization that you will be spending the night in the wilderness begins to sets in. Being prepared for this type of situation and having a well established plan could mean the difference between life and death. That is why at the “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup, our chief aim is to help people build their knowledge of wilderness survival skills.

The Aim of this Meetup Group is to teach you the skills needed to survive and thrive in the wilderness and woodlands.  You will learn the skills and techniques to light fires, identify edible plants, build shelters, make traps and snares, purify water, prepare rabbit, fish and birds, use knives and saws safely and efficiently and navigate around the country.

Upon leaning these skills members will understand how to: become self sufficient in the wilderness, formulate a concrete plan to getting rescued safely when lost or injured and build outdoor leadership/confidence skills.

The “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup strongly believe a subject must be mastered before it can be taught; therefore, my teaching methods have been developed through years of education, practice, experiences and dedication of me and I will structure our lesson around a fundamental survival principle commonly known as the Rules of 3.

So what is the Rules of 3?

The rules of 3 are the guidelines that states you cannot survive more than:

• 3 Minutes without air

• 3 Hours without shelter or proper clothing

• 3 Days without water

• 3 Weeks without food


Classes we host:

• Wilderness Survival Kits

• Shelter Building

• Wild Edible Plants

• Tracking

• Fire Starting

• Water Purification

• Land Navigation

• First Aid

• Self defense

And much much more…

Important notice:

• This is not a group for "Meetup Group collectors"

• We are a group of active members

• Members who are not actively participating are not eligible

• Members who do not actively participate are automatically excluded


Minimum age

• The minimum age is 18 years, or 10 years if acompanied by at least one responsible adult!!!

• Participants must be able to handle safetly a KNIFE and FIRE.


Responsibility and liability

• Kolonok Bushcraft Survival or I, assume no liability for accidents or damage. Insurance and 3th part liability is the responsibility of each individual participant or legal representative.

• With the registration you accept this term or condition.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
This platform proposes to share info and experiences in construction with natural materials. And occasionally give a hand on your building site. I have learnt several techniques to build a house with natural materials, and I wish to spread this knowledge to anyone interested in living in a more healthy and natural environment.
We will discuss: clay plasters, lime mortar and lime plasters, natural fibers as insulation, how to build walls without cement, the plus and minus of Tadelakt bathrooms, natural paints, dry stone wall for your garden, straw bale walls, rammed earth walls.
We will discuss where to get natural materials, which one to get, and others on the market that are not 100% natural.
This knowledge is best when you repair an ancient house, or build a new natural house, but it can also be applied to a "modern house" that is not really natural.
Anyone who has experienced in this field is here welcome to share its knowledge too.
Looking forward to meeting you,
Peace,
Catherine
name: Build your natural house!

The group aims to exchange techniques, ideas and opportunities in the filed of aerial cinematography. The plan is as follows: 

First meeting: Get to know each other and plan a drone-trip (1 day) to a location where we can try out new techniques and explore our drones (e.g. Swiss mountains).

Second meeting: Day-trip to a location where it is legal, safe and pretty to fly out drones This group is aimed for professional or semi-professional drone pilots in Switzerland, whatever that means ;-). I own a DJI Inspire 2 X7 16 mm and am looking for other enthusiasts to fly with and share knowledge :-)

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Could this be you?: "Hi, my name is Bob, and I'm a CNC-builder-aholic." Alone, struggling to turn a CNC dream into some kind of reality? Trying to figure out which is the best ball or ACME screw, linear rail, stepper or servo system, Makerslide or Bosch-Rexroth profile, epoxy concrete base or MDF, Chinese high speed spindle or Kress router or diy brushless motor hack, ... (you know the list goes on).  Finally a support group for those suffering from this condition. Maybe together we can push our designs from our heads to our benchtops.

Although 3D printers could technically be called a computer numerically controlled device, this group is more about machines pushing more or much more weight--a milling device/router, a plasma cutter, a laser cutter, etc.  3D printers are also interesting to discuss but wouldn't be the main focus..
name: CNC Builders Basel

description:
This is a group for anybody who loves sewing and textile work. Social Fabric (www.socialfabric.ch) is a community oriented-place in Zürich that supports the use of textiles and clothing that have a small ecological and social footprint. At Social Fabric, we offer courses and community events that help people to build a new relationship to their clothes. 

We also have a project that supports refugee integration by encouraging refugees to create and develop their own products that have a textile-oriented theme. Our long term goal with this project is to both employ refugees as producers, and to enable refugee entrepreneurs. 

We are also on Facebook: Social Fabric page and Social Fabric group – like and join!

On Twitter we are @iamsocialfabric.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Ikebana ist eine Form der Schulung, die Einblick in die Schönheit des Lebens gewährt.

Ikebana Schule Caroline Vögele-Ott

Dies ist eine Gruppe für alle die sich gerne mit Blumen, natürlichem Pflanzenmaterial und schönen Gefässen beschäftigen und eine sinnliche Beziehung zur Natur pflegen. Ob Anfänger oder Fortgeschritten, alle sind willkommen, entweder meine Anfängerkurse zu besuchen oder in der Erfahrungsgruppe mitzumachen. Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, um Ikebana allen Interessierten ohne Vorkenntnisse zugänglich zu machen und die bereits erfahrenen IkebanistiInnen zum Austausch und gemeinsamen Experimentieren zu ermuntern. Ich freue mich auf viel sinnliche, blumige und kreative Meetings und kleine Erleuchtungsmomente für Anfänger.

Ich selber nehem regelmässig an verschiedenen internationalen Workshops teil und bilde mich immer weiter. Wer einmal erlebt hat wie wertvoll dieses schaffen mit Blumen und Zweigen ist, kann für den Rest seines Lebens nicht mehr davon ablassen. So ist es mir gegangen, als ich vor über 12 Jahren angefangen habe. Es wird Teil des Alltags. Die Betrachtung und die Wahrnehmung der Natur wird zu einem bereichernden Erlebnis. Der Wunsch nach Ordnung im eigenen Wohnraum ist eine Nebenerscheinung die Ikebana ganz unbemerkt fördert und entstehen lässt. Für mich ist Ikebana auch eine Form von "urban Gardening". Sie bringt einen Ausschnitt der Natrur in Deinen Wohnraum und verzaubert ihn jedes Mal von neuem! 

Bitte finde auf folgendem Link noch ausführlichere Informationen zu meiner Schule:

http://www.caroline-voegele.ch/index.php?id...

Herzlichst

Caroline
name: Zürich Ohara Ikebana, the art of japanese flower arrangement

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Kolonok (zool.), Siberian Weasel


"The less a man carries in his pack, the more he must carry in his head" - Horace Kephart


Have you ever thought about what you would do if you became lost while on a day hike? How about if you injured yourself out from civilization and were unable to move? Then, all too quickly dusk approaches and the realization that you will be spending the night in the wilderness begins to sets in. Being prepared for this type of situation and having a well established plan could mean the difference between life and death. That is why at the “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup, our chief aim is to help people build their knowledge of wilderness survival skills.

The Aim of this Meetup Group is to teach you the skills needed to survive and thrive in the wilderness and woodlands.  You will learn the skills and techniques to light fires, identify edible plants, build shelters, make traps and snares, purify water, prepare rabbit, fish and birds, use knives and saws safely and efficiently and navigate around the country.

Upon leaning these skills members will understand how to: become self sufficient in the wilderness, formulate a concrete plan to getting rescued safely when lost or injured and build outdoor leadership/confidence skills.

The “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup strongly believe a subject must be mastered before it can be taught; therefore, my teaching methods have been developed through years of education, practice, experiences and dedication of me and I will structure our lesson around a fundamental survival principle commonly known as the Rules of 3.

So what is the Rules of 3?

The rules of 3 are the guidelines that states you cannot survive more than:

• 3 Minutes without air

• 3 Hours without shelter or proper clothing

• 3 Days without water

• 3 Weeks without food


Classes we host:

• Wilderness Survival Kits

• Shelter Building

• Wild Edible Plants

• Tracking

• Fire Starting

• Water Purification

• Land Navigation

• First Aid

• Self defense

And much much more…

Important notice:

• This is not a group for "Meetup Group collectors"

• We are a group of active members

• Members who are not actively participating are not eligible

• Members who do not actively participate are automatically excluded


Minimum age

• The minimum age is 18 years, or 10 years if acompanied by at least one responsible adult!!!

• Participants must be able to handle safetly a KNIFE and FIRE.


Responsibility and liability

• Kolonok Bushcraft Survival or I, assume no liability for accidents or damage. Insurance and 3th part liability is the responsibility of each individual participant or legal representative.

• With the registration you accept this term or condition.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
This platform proposes to share info and experiences in construction with natural materials. And occasionally give a hand on your building site. I have learnt several techniques to build a house with natural materials, and I wish to spread this knowledge to anyone interested in living in a more healthy and natural environment.
We will discuss: clay plasters, lime mortar and lime plasters, natural fibers as insulation, how to build walls without cement, the plus and minus of Tadelakt bathrooms, natural paints, dry stone wall for your garden, straw bale walls, rammed earth walls.
We will discuss where to get natural materials, which one to get, and others on the market that are not 100% natural.
This knowledge is best when you repair an ancient house, or build a new natural house, but it can also be applied to a "modern house" that is not really natural.
Anyone who has experienced in this field is here welcome to share its knowledge too.
Looking forward to meeting you,
Peace,
Catherine
name: Build your natural house!

description:
The group aims to exchange techniques, ideas and opportunities in the filed of aerial cinematography. The plan is as follows: 

First meeting: Get to know each other and plan a drone-trip (1 day) to a location where we can try out new techniques and explore our drones (e.g. Swiss mountains).

Second meeting: Day-trip to a location where it is legal, safe and pretty to fly out drones This group is aimed for professional or semi-professional drone pilots in Switzerland, whatever that means ;-). I own a DJI Inspire 2 X7 16 mm and am looking for other enthusiasts to fly with and share knowledge :-)

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Could this be you?: "Hi, my name is Bob, and I'm a CNC-builder-aholic." Alone, struggling to turn a CNC dream into some kind of reality? Trying to figure out which is the best ball or ACME screw, linear rail, stepper or servo system, Makerslide or Bosch-Rexroth profile, epoxy concrete base or MDF, Chinese high speed spindle or Kress router or diy brushless motor hack, ... (you know the list goes on).  Finally a support group for those suffering from this condition. Maybe together we can push our designs from our heads to our benchtops.

Although 3D printers could technically be called a computer numerically controlled device, this group is more about machines pushing more or much more weight--a milling device/router, a plasma cutter, a laser cutter, etc.  3D printers are also interesting to discuss but wouldn't be the main focus..
name: CNC Builders Basel

description:
This is a group for anybody who loves sewing and textile work. Social Fabric (www.socialfabric.ch) is a community oriented-place in Zürich that supports the use of textiles and clothing that have a small ecological and social footprint. At Social Fabric, we offer courses and community events that help people to build a new relationship to their clothes. 

We also have a project that supports refugee integration by encouraging refugees to create and develop their own products that have a textile-oriented theme. Our long term goal with this project is to both employ refugees as producers, and to enable refugee entrepreneurs. 

We are also on Facebook: Social Fabric page and Social Fabric group – like and join!

On Twitter we are @iamsocialfabric.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Ikebana ist eine Form der Schulung, die Einblick in die Schönheit des Lebens gewährt.

Ikebana Schule Caroline Vögele-Ott

Dies ist eine Gruppe für alle die sich gerne mit Blumen, natürlichem Pflanzenmaterial und schönen Gefässen beschäftigen und eine sinnliche Beziehung zur Natur pflegen. Ob Anfänger oder Fortgeschritten, alle sind willkommen, entweder meine Anfängerkurse zu besuchen oder in der Erfahrungsgruppe mitzumachen. Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, um Ikebana allen Interessierten ohne Vorkenntnisse zugänglich zu machen und die bereits erfahrenen IkebanistiInnen zum Austausch und gemeinsamen Experimentieren zu ermuntern. Ich freue mich auf viel sinnliche, blumige und kreative Meetings und kleine Erleuchtungsmomente für Anfänger.

Ich selber nehem regelmässig an verschiedenen internationalen Workshops teil und bilde mich immer weiter. Wer einmal erlebt hat wie wertvoll dieses schaffen mit Blumen und Zweigen ist, kann für den Rest seines Lebens nicht mehr davon ablassen. So ist es mir gegangen, als ich vor über 12 Jahren angefangen habe. Es wird Teil des Alltags. Die Betrachtung und die Wahrnehmung der Natur wird zu einem bereichernden Erlebnis. Der Wunsch nach Ordnung im eigenen Wohnraum ist eine Nebenerscheinung die Ikebana ganz unbemerkt fördert und entstehen lässt. Für mich ist Ikebana auch eine Form von "urban Gardening". Sie bringt einen Ausschnitt der Natrur in Deinen Wohnraum und verzaubert ihn jedes Mal von neuem! 

Bitte finde auf folgendem Link noch ausführlichere Informationen zu meiner Schule:

http://www.caroline-voegele.ch/index.php?id...

Herzlichst

Caroline
name: Zürich Ohara Ikebana, the art of japanese flower arrangement

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Kolonok (zool.), Siberian Weasel


"The less a man carries in his pack, the more he must carry in his head" - Horace Kephart


Have you ever thought about what you would do if you became lost while on a day hike? How about if you injured yourself out from civilization and were unable to move? Then, all too quickly dusk approaches and the realization that you will be spending the night in the wilderness begins to sets in. Being prepared for this type of situation and having a well established plan could mean the difference between life and death. That is why at the “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup, our chief aim is to help people build their knowledge of wilderness survival skills.

The Aim of this Meetup Group is to teach you the skills needed to survive and thrive in the wilderness and woodlands.  You will learn the skills and techniques to light fires, identify edible plants, build shelters, make traps and snares, purify water, prepare rabbit, fish and birds, use knives and saws safely and efficiently and navigate around the country.

Upon leaning these skills members will understand how to: become self sufficient in the wilderness, formulate a concrete plan to getting rescued safely when lost or injured and build outdoor leadership/confidence skills.

The “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup strongly believe a subject must be mastered before it can be taught; therefore, my teaching methods have been developed through years of education, practice, experiences and dedication of me and I will structure our lesson around a fundamental survival principle commonly known as the Rules of 3.

So what is the Rules of 3?

The rules of 3 are the guidelines that states you cannot survive more than:

• 3 Minutes without air

• 3 Hours without shelter or proper clothing

• 3 Days without water

• 3 Weeks without food


Classes we host:

• Wilderness Survival Kits

• Shelter Building

• Wild Edible Plants

• Tracking

• Fire Starting

• Water Purification

• Land Navigation

• First Aid

• Self defense

And much much more…

Important notice:

• This is not a group for "Meetup Group collectors"

• We are a group of active members

• Members who are not actively participating are not eligible

• Members who do not actively participate are automatically excluded


Minimum age

• The minimum age is 18 years, or 10 years if acompanied by at least one responsible adult!!!

• Participants must be able to handle safetly a KNIFE and FIRE.


Responsibility and liability

• Kolonok Bushcraft Survival or I, assume no liability for accidents or damage. Insurance and 3th part liability is the responsibility of each individual participant or legal representative.

• With the registration you accept this term or condition.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
This platform proposes to share info and experiences in construction with natural materials. And occasionally give a hand on your building site. I have learnt several techniques to build a house with natural materials, and I wish to spread this knowledge to anyone interested in living in a more healthy and natural environment.
We will discuss: clay plasters, lime mortar and lime plasters, natural fibers as insulation, how to build walls without cement, the plus and minus of Tadelakt bathrooms, natural paints, dry stone wall for your garden, straw bale walls, rammed earth walls.
We will discuss where to get natural materials, which one to get, and others on the market that are not 100% natural.
This knowledge is best when you repair an ancient house, or build a new natural house, but it can also be applied to a "modern house" that is not really natural.
Anyone who has experienced in this field is here welcome to share its knowledge too.
Looking forward to meeting you,
Peace,
Catherine

The group aims to exchange techniques, ideas and opportunities in the filed of aerial cinematography. The plan is as follows: 

First meeting: Get to know each other and plan a drone-trip (1 day) to a location where we can try out new techniques and explore our drones (e.g. Swiss mountains).

Second meeting: Day-trip to a location where it is legal, safe and pretty to fly out drones This group is aimed for professional or semi-professional drone pilots in Switzerland, whatever that means ;-). description:
Vous aimez la décoration d’intérieur, les tendances déco, l’aménagement d’intérieur, vous voulez que votre intérieur vous ressemble et soit unique, mais vous vous heurtez à un marché qui propose des milliers de solutions et vous êtes parfois perdu(e)s dans tout ce choix.

J’aide les personnes comme vous qui veulent faire de leur espace de vie un intérieur unique et harmonieux, je les accompagne pour qu’elles aient la fierté de le réaliser elle-même.

Passionnée par ce métier de coach déco, je vous propose de passer un bon moment ensemble à partager sur des problématiques que l’on rencontre quand on veut aménager, valoriser son intérieur.

J’ai donc créé pour vous
---- LES MERCREDIS POUR MON ESPACE DE VIE ----

-. 1 mercredi par mois
-. 1 thème
-. Une discussion en toute décontraction sur vos problématiques sur le thème du mois
-. Des solutions pratiques et simples à appliquées.

Je me réjouis de vous rencontrer !

A bientôt

Floriane
Révélatrice d’espace de vie

description:
This is a group for anybody who loves sewing and textile work. Social Fabric (www.socialfabric.ch) is a community oriented-place in Zürich that supports the use of textiles and clothing that have a small ecological and social footprint. At Social Fabric, we offer courses and community events that help people to build a new relationship to their clothes. 

We also have a project that supports refugee integration by encouraging refugees to create and develop their own products that have a textile-oriented theme. Our long term goal with this project is to both employ refugees as producers, and to enable refugee entrepreneurs. 

We are also on Facebook: Social Fabric page and Social Fabric group – like and join!

On Twitter we are @iamsocialfabric.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Ikebana ist eine Form der Schulung, die Einblick in die Schönheit des Lebens gewährt.

Ikebana Schule Caroline Vögele-Ott

Dies ist eine Gruppe für alle die sich gerne mit Blumen, natürlichem Pflanzenmaterial und schönen Gefässen beschäftigen und eine sinnliche Beziehung zur Natur pflegen. Ob Anfänger oder Fortgeschritten, alle sind willkommen, entweder meine Anfängerkurse zu besuchen oder in der Erfahrungsgruppe mitzumachen. Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, um Ikebana allen Interessierten ohne Vorkenntnisse zugänglich zu machen und die bereits erfahrenen IkebanistiInnen zum Austausch und gemeinsamen Experimentieren zu ermuntern. Ich freue mich auf viel sinnliche, blumige und kreative Meetings und kleine Erleuchtungsmomente für Anfänger.

Ich selber nehem regelmässig an verschiedenen internationalen Workshops teil und bilde mich immer weiter. Wer einmal erlebt hat wie wertvoll dieses schaffen mit Blumen und Zweigen ist, kann für den Rest seines Lebens nicht mehr davon ablassen. So ist es mir gegangen, als ich vor über 12 Jahren angefangen habe. Es wird Teil des Alltags. Die Betrachtung und die Wahrnehmung der Natur wird zu einem bereichernden Erlebnis. Der Wunsch nach Ordnung im eigenen Wohnraum ist eine Nebenerscheinung die Ikebana ganz unbemerkt fördert und entstehen lässt. Für mich ist Ikebana auch eine Form von "urban Gardening". Sie bringt einen Ausschnitt der Natrur in Deinen Wohnraum und verzaubert ihn jedes Mal von neuem! 

Bitte finde auf folgendem Link noch ausführlichere Informationen zu meiner Schule:

http://www.caroline-voegele.ch/index.php?id...

Herzlichst

Caroline
name: Zürich Ohara Ikebana, the art of japanese flower arrangement

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Kolonok (zool.), Siberian Weasel


"The less a man carries in his pack, the more he must carry in his head" - Horace Kephart


Have you ever thought about what you would do if you became lost while on a day hike? How about if you injured yourself out from civilization and were unable to move? Then, all too quickly dusk approaches and the realization that you will be spending the night in the wilderness begins to sets in. Being prepared for this type of situation and having a well established plan could mean the difference between life and death. That is why at the “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup, our chief aim is to help people build their knowledge of wilderness survival skills.

The Aim of this Meetup Group is to teach you the skills needed to survive and thrive in the wilderness and woodlands.  You will learn the skills and techniques to light fires, identify edible plants, build shelters, make traps and snares, purify water, prepare rabbit, fish and birds, use knives and saws safely and efficiently and navigate around the country.

Upon leaning these skills members will understand how to: become self sufficient in the wilderness, formulate a concrete plan to getting rescued safely when lost or injured and build outdoor leadership/confidence skills.

The “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup strongly believe a subject must be mastered before it can be taught; therefore, my teaching methods have been developed through years of education, practice, experiences and dedication of me and I will structure our lesson around a fundamental survival principle commonly known as the Rules of 3.

So what is the Rules of 3?

The rules of 3 are the guidelines that states you cannot survive more than:

• 3 Minutes without air

• 3 Hours without shelter or proper clothing

• 3 Days without water

• 3 Weeks without food


Classes we host:

• Wilderness Survival Kits

• Shelter Building

• Wild Edible Plants

• Tracking

• Fire Starting

• Water Purification

• Land Navigation

• First Aid

• Self defense

And much much more…

Important notice:

• This is not a group for "Meetup Group collectors"

• We are a group of active members

• Members who are not actively participating are not eligible

• Members who do not actively participate are automatically excluded


Minimum age

• The minimum age is 18 years, or 10 years if acompanied by at least one responsible adult!!!

• Participants must be able to handle safetly a KNIFE and FIRE.


Responsibility and liability

• Kolonok Bushcraft Survival or I, assume no liability for accidents or damage. Insurance and 3th part liability is the responsibility of each individual participant or legal representative.

• With the registration you accept this term or condition.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
This platform proposes to share info and experiences in construction with natural materials. And occasionally give a hand on your building site. I have learnt several techniques to build a house with natural materials, and I wish to spread this knowledge to anyone interested in living in a more healthy and natural environment.
We will discuss: clay plasters, lime mortar and lime plasters, natural fibers as insulation, how to build walls without cement, the plus and minus of Tadelakt bathrooms, natural paints, dry stone wall for your garden, straw bale walls, rammed earth walls.
We will discuss where to get natural materials, which one to get, and others on the market that are not 100% natural.
This knowledge is best when you repair an ancient house, or build a new natural house, but it can also be applied to a "modern house" that is not really natural.
Anyone who has experienced in this field is here welcome to share its knowledge too.
Looking forward to meeting you,
Peace,
Catherine

description:
The group aims to exchange techniques, ideas and opportunities in the filed of aerial cinematography. The plan is as follows: 

First meeting: Get to know each other and plan a drone-trip (1 day) to a location where we can try out new techniques and explore our drones (e.g. Swiss mountains).

Second meeting: Day-trip to a location where it is legal, safe and pretty to fly out drones This group is aimed for professional or semi-professional drone pilots in Switzerland, whatever that means ;-). I own a DJI Inspire 2 X7 16 mm and am looking for other enthusiasts to fly with and share knowledge :-)

TheBeehive is an atelier for kids and women created by two young mothers who are passionate about making things… sewing, painting, working with wood, cement and whatever else they can get their hands on.
The only limits that we fix for ourselves are those of our imagination.
We offer organised workshops for kids (with or without parent) and women throughout the week and on saturdays.
The goal is for women to have a place to go to and create whatever their hearts desire and at the same time network with other women and to have a fun time. And for kids to broaden their imaginations with arts & crafts and make new friends....

description:
This is a group for anybody who loves sewing and textile work. Social Fabric (www.socialfabric.ch) is a community oriented-place in Zürich that supports the use of textiles and clothing that have a small ecological and social footprint. At Social Fabric, we offer courses and community events that help people to build a new relationship to their clothes. 

We also have a project that supports refugee integration by encouraging refugees to create and develop their own products that have a textile-oriented theme. Our long term goal with this project is to both employ refugees as producers, and to enable refugee entrepreneurs. 

We are also on Facebook: Social Fabric page and Social Fabric group – like and join!

On Twitter we are @iamsocialfabric.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Ikebana ist eine Form der Schulung, die Einblick in die Schönheit des Lebens gewährt.

Ikebana Schule Caroline Vögele-Ott

Dies ist eine Gruppe für alle die sich gerne mit Blumen, natürlichem Pflanzenmaterial und schönen Gefässen beschäftigen und eine sinnliche Beziehung zur Natur pflegen. Ob Anfänger oder Fortgeschritten, alle sind willkommen, entweder meine Anfängerkurse zu besuchen oder in der Erfahrungsgruppe mitzumachen. Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, um Ikebana allen Interessierten ohne Vorkenntnisse zugänglich zu machen und die bereits erfahrenen IkebanistiInnen zum Austausch und gemeinsamen Experimentieren zu ermuntern. Ich freue mich auf viel sinnliche, blumige und kreative Meetings und kleine Erleuchtungsmomente für Anfänger.

Ich selber nehem regelmässig an verschiedenen internationalen Workshops teil und bilde mich immer weiter. Wer einmal erlebt hat wie wertvoll dieses schaffen mit Blumen und Zweigen ist, kann für den Rest seines Lebens nicht mehr davon ablassen. So ist es mir gegangen, als ich vor über 12 Jahren angefangen habe. Es wird Teil des Alltags. Die Betrachtung und die Wahrnehmung der Natur wird zu einem bereichernden Erlebnis. Der Wunsch nach Ordnung im eigenen Wohnraum ist eine Nebenerscheinung die Ikebana ganz unbemerkt fördert und entstehen lässt. Für mich ist Ikebana auch eine Form von "urban Gardening". Sie bringt einen Ausschnitt der Natrur in Deinen Wohnraum und verzaubert ihn jedes Mal von neuem! 

Bitte finde auf folgendem Link noch ausführlichere Informationen zu meiner Schule:

http://www.caroline-voegele.ch/index.php?id...

Herzlichst

Caroline
name: Zürich Ohara Ikebana, the art of japanese flower arrangement

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
Kolonok (zool.), Siberian Weasel


"The less a man carries in his pack, the more he must carry in his head" - Horace Kephart


Have you ever thought about what you would do if you became lost while on a day hike? How about if you injured yourself out from civilization and were unable to move? Then, all too quickly dusk approaches and the realization that you will be spending the night in the wilderness begins to sets in. Being prepared for this type of situation and having a well established plan could mean the difference between life and death. That is why at the “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup, our chief aim is to help people build their knowledge of wilderness survival skills.

The Aim of this Meetup Group is to teach you the skills needed to survive and thrive in the wilderness and woodlands.  You will learn the skills and techniques to light fires, identify edible plants, build shelters, make traps and snares, purify water, prepare rabbit, fish and birds, use knives and saws safely and efficiently and navigate around the country.

Upon leaning these skills members will understand how to: become self sufficient in the wilderness, formulate a concrete plan to getting rescued safely when lost or injured and build outdoor leadership/confidence skills.

The “Kolonok Bushcraft Survival” Meetup strongly believe a subject must be mastered before it can be taught; therefore, my teaching methods have been developed through years of education, practice, experiences and dedication of me and I will structure our lesson around a fundamental survival principle commonly known as the Rules of 3.

So what is the Rules of 3?

The rules of 3 are the guidelines that states you cannot survive more than:

• 3 Minutes without air

• 3 Hours without shelter or proper clothing

• 3 Days without water

• 3 Weeks without food


Classes we host:

• Wilderness Survival Kits

• Shelter Building

• Wild Edible Plants

• Tracking

• Fire Starting

• Water Purification

• Land Navigation

• First Aid

• Self defense

And much much more…

Important notice:

• This is not a group for "Meetup Group collectors"

• We are a group of active members

• Members who are not actively participating are not eligible

• Members who do not actively participate are automatically excluded


Minimum age

• The minimum age is 18 years, or 10 years if acompanied by at least one responsible adult!!!

• Participants must be able to handle safetly a KNIFE and FIRE.


Responsibility and liability

• Kolonok Bushcraft Survival or I, assume no liability for accidents or damage. Insurance and 3th part liability is the responsibility of each individual participant or legal representative.

• With the registration you accept this term or condition.

category.name: hobbies/crafts
description:
This platform proposes to share info and experiences in construction with natural materials. And occasionally give a hand on your building site. I have learnt several techniques to build a house with natural materials, and I wish to spread this knowledge to anyone interested in living in a more healthy and natural environment.
We will discuss: clay plasters, lime mortar and lime plasters, natural fibers as insulation, how to build walls without cement, the plus and minus of Tadelakt bathrooms, natural paints, dry stone wall for your garden, straw bale walls, rammed earth walls.
We will discuss where to get natural materials, which one to get, and others on the market that are not 100% natural.
This knowledge is best when you repair an ancient house, or build a new natural house, but it can also be applied to a "modern house" that is not really natural.
Anyone who has experienced in this field is here welcome to share its knowledge too.
Looking forward to meeting you,
Peace,
Catherine
name: Build your natural house!

The group aims to exchange techniques, ideas and opportunities in the filed of aerial cinematography. The plan is as follows: 

First meeting: Get to know each other and plan a drone-trip (1 day) to a location where we can try out new techniques and explore our drones (e.g. Swiss mountains).

Second meeting: Day-trip to a location where it is legal, safe and pretty to fly out drones This group is aimed for professional or semi-professional drone pilots in Switzerland, whatever that means ;-). description:
Vous aimez la décoration d’intérieur, les tendances déco, l’aménagement d’intérieur, vous voulez que votre intérieur vous ressemble et soit unique, mais vous vous heurtez à un marché qui propose des milliers de solutions et vous êtes parfois perdu(e)s dans tout ce choix.

J’aide les personnes comme vous qui veulent faire de leur espace de vie un intérieur unique et harmonieux, je les accompagne pour qu’elles aient la fierté de le réaliser elle-même.

Passionnée par ce métier de coach déco, je vous propose de passer un bon moment ensemble à partager sur des problématiques que l’on rencontre quand on veut aménager, valoriser son intérieur.

J’ai donc créé pour vous
---- LES MERCREDIS POUR MON ESPACE DE VIE ----

-. 1 mercredi par mois
-. 1 thème
-. Une discussion en toute décontraction sur vos problématiques sur le thème du mois
-. Des solutions pratiques et simples à appliquées.

Je me réjouis de vous rencontrer !

A bientôt

Floriane
Révélatrice d’espace de vie
